<br>
Why does there HAVE to be an uncreated creator? A conscience? This is only LOGICAL if you limit yourself to the position that we were created by God, and that he was created by something, and that being was created by something else, ad naseam.<br>
<br>
If you allow yourself to look at theories outside of God as creator, you might have better luck trying to formulate answers to these questions. For example: perhaps we were simply CREATED by Nature. Nature provided energy, matter, and an endless supply of time. Combinations of these three ingredients provided the building blocks of life, as well as an habitable environment in which life could gain a foothold, and eventually thrive.<br>
<br>
The odds that we are here are astronomical. It's like we won the lottery to BE in a lottery, to BE in another lottery, etc., etc., and somehow won. We struggle to find answers to how we came to be here, and when they don't come readily, it's sometimes easier to simply assign it all to a higher, benevolent being. Someone watching out for us so to speak. For some, the alternative is simply too overwhelming to consider.<br>
<br>
There may be a God(s). I really don't know. I will say that I highly doubt it. For me, too many of the answers found in religion simply boil down to &quot;because I said so&quot;. Those aren't the kinds of answers I'm looking for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uvibesjoker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ViBeSJoKeR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/30/01 8:42:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=281.topic&index=89>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/vibes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmmm</span><hr size=1> I have to return to the part where I posted earlier that mankind only uses a small percentage of his mind and that if we would use it to our maximum ability we might turn into Gods (yes farfetched I know).<br>
